Architecture plan for Issue #149: Show the two faction tally boxes side-by-side in one row on phone

Repository shape:
- Monorepo with a Vite/React frontend in frontend/, Rust Axum backend in backend/, and shared TypeScript DTO/contracts in shared/.
- This issue is purely presentational and should be implemented in the frontend styling layer, primarily frontend/src/styles.css. The React markup in frontend/src/App.tsx already renders the Live Faction Tallies section with a shared .tlhn-network-tally-grid wrapper and two FactionTallyDisplay cards.
- No backend API, database, or shared DTO changes are expected. Faction counts continue to be fetched from GET /api/factions/counts and typed by shared/src/factions.ts.

Issue dependency analysis:
- There is only one issue in this batch: #149.
- It has no dependencies and can be implemented independently.
- It builds on the existing responsive network layout and tally card CSS from prior mobile layout work.

Key design decisions:
- Keep the desktop/tablet layout unchanged while making the base/mobile .tlhn-network-tally-grid use two columns instead of stacked cards.
- Prefer a CSS-only change: set the tally grid to two equal columns at base width, preserving existing gap and any sm:/desktop overrides unless they need slight adjustment.
- If the cards are too wide on narrow phones, tighten internal mobile-only spacing, min-height, label size, and count size in the existing tally-card selectors rather than changing API data or component structure.
- Preserve accessibility and semantic markup: the section heading and two faction cards remain unchanged in React.
- Validate with frontend build/typecheck/lint where available. Rust backend behavior is unaffected.
